<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 92 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: A burning land issue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
IF SOMEONE burnt garden refuse on a small piece of land on a roadside bank
outside the boundary of his property for a few days each year, would he be
able to claim adverse ownership after 12 years?
No. the use would not amount to adverse possession, and in fact would not
even constitute possession at all.
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All inquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
