<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JAN 92 / The Lex Column: Ratners
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ratners shares have fallen so far in recent months that they barely reacted
to the threatened move into Chapter 11 of Zale, the leading US jeweller.
Granted, they had already dropped by more than 10 per cent yesterday on
worries about the group's Christmas trading performance. But Zale's angry
creditors have served an unwelcome reminder to the market that Ratners is
vulnerable to more than the depressed UK high street. Its US business is an
obvious candidate for sale should the group require a refinancing of its
debts. While the issue of what that business might fetch is more germane
than ever, the likely figure is shrinking all the time. Zale's decline will
surely benefit Ratners in the long term. The question is whether Ratners has
enough time in hand.
