FT  03 JAN 92 / Duracell to close Crawley plant
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DURACELL, the US battery group, is to shed 320 jobs at its plant in Crawley,
West Sussex, as it rationalises its European manufacturing and distribution
operations.
The company will wind down the components plant by August and transfer
production to one centre in Aarschot, Belgium, where it runs the biggest
alkaline battery factory in the world.
Duracell had been considering the move for many months but decided to close
the Crawley plant only after it failed to find space to expand capacity.
Duracell employs 750 people in the UK, with 650 based at the components
plant and technical centre in Crawley.
