<TEXT>
JAPAN'S leading trading houses, Sumitomo Corporation and Nissho Iwai
Corporation, each evaded at least Y1bn (Pounds 4.27m) in taxes between March
1987 and March 1989, a Japanese news agency reported, Reuter writes from
Tokyo.
Kyodo news agency said on Wednesday that the Osaka Regional Taxation Bureau
