FT  02 JAN 92 / Training plea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR NORMAN Lamont, the chancellor, should plan for more spending on
education, training and transport in his March Budget rather than cut taxes,
the British Institute of Management says.
The suggestions were based on the responses of 730 managers to a
