<TEXT>
Four Rwandan opposition parties have called on supporters to hold a protest
march against the formation of a new coalition government which excludes
them, Reuter reports from Kigali. Prime Minister Sylvestre Nsanzimana on
Monday announced a new cabinet in which all but one of the 17 posts are
taken up by members of the ruling party.
</TEXT>
